    "body": "### Problem\n\nmemory leak\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n1. Build master with ASAN & LSAN\n2. save file:\n ```lua\n local buf  = vim.api.nvim_create_buf(false, true)\n local chan = vim.api.nvim_open_term(buf, {})\n vim.api.nvim_create_autocmd('TermRequest', { buffer = buf, callback = function() end })\n vim.api.nvim_chan_send(chan, '\\x1b]7;file:///a\\x1b\\\\')\n vim.api.nvim_chan_send(chan, '\\x1b]7;file:///b\\x1b\\\\')\n vim.api.nvim_buf_delete(buf, { force = true })\n```\n3. `ASAN_OPTIONS=detect_leaks=1 <pathtonvim>/nvim --headless --clean -c 'luafile /tmp/nvim-termreq-leak.lua' -c 'qa!'`\n\n```\n=================================================================\n==2038791==ERROR: LeakSanitizer: detected memory leaks\n\nDirect leak of 24 byte(s) in 1 object(s) allocated from:\n    #0 0x7f843e721c2b in malloc (/nix/store/ihpdbhy4rfxaixiamyb588zfc3vj19al-gcc-15.2.0-lib/lib/libasan.so.8+0x121c2b)\n    #1 0x556e02e272b3 in try_malloc /tmp/neovim/bughunt/src/nvim/memory.c:113\n    #2 0x556e02e273c8 in xmalloc /tmp/neovim/bughunt/src/nvim/memory.c:147\n    #3 0x556e0317e848 in schedule_termrequest /tmp/neovim/bughunt/src/nvim/terminal.c:304\n    #4 0x556e03180007 in on_osc /tmp/neovim/bughunt/src/nvim/terminal.c:367\n    #5 0x556e0328f8d8 in on_osc /tmp/neovim/bughunt/src/nvim/vterm/state.c:1985\n    #6 0x556e03272876 in string_fragment /tmp/neovim/bughunt/src/nvim/vterm/parser.c:89\n    #7 0x556e0327321a in vterm_input_write /tmp/neovim/bughunt/src/nvim/vterm/parser.c:323\n    #8 0x556e0318d347 in terminal_receive /tmp/neovim/bughunt/src/nvim/terminal.c:1378\n    #9 0x556e0298fca0 in channel_send /tmp/neovim/bughunt/src/nvim/channel.c:638\n    #10 0x556e02903b91 in nvim_chan_send /tmp/neovim/bughunt/src/nvim/api/vim.c:1275\n    #11 0x556e02d1f1d9 in nlua_api_nvim_chan_send /tmp/neovim/bughunt/asanbuild/src/nvim/auto/lua_api_c_bindings.generated.h:6159\n    #12 0x556e03381545 in lj_BC_FUNCC (/tmp/neovim/bughunt/asanbuild/bin/nvim+0x180a545)\n\nSUMMARY: AddressSanitizer: 24 byte(s) leaked in 1 allocation(s).\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nno leak\n\n***NOTE***: I already have a fix for this. I'm putting it up rn\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.12\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno (N/A)\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nnixos\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\nlocal build",
